  "texts": [
    "HSI involves capturing a wide range of electromagnetic wavelengths, often spanning tens or hundreds of bands.",
    "This capability allows HSI to provide image data and detailed spectral information unique to different objects, making it highly effective in identifying specific materials or conditions.",
    "However, traditional HSI systems suffer from low spatial resolution, which limits their utility.",
    "In contrast, standard RGB images offer rich spatial detail but contain only three spectral channels, i.e., red, green, and blue, in the visible range (400-700 nm).",
    "Due to limited spectral information, RGB images can be used for applications that require spectral information within the visible range."
  ],
